sentences.english: Stranahan, a graduate student at Princeton University in New Jersey.
sentences.chinese: 是新澤西州普林斯頓大學的畢業生。

sentences.english: There is golf-ball-size hail in New Jersey today.
sentences.chinese: 新澤西州今日下起高爾夫球大小的冰雹。

sentences.english: A little further south, look at these New Jersey homes.
sentences.chinese: 往南去，我們來看看新澤西州的家庭。

sentences.english: Actually I did grow up in Edison, New Jersey.
sentences.chinese: 我是在新澤西州的愛迪生市長大的。

sentences.english: bury an urn in Elizabeth New Jersey, B'nai Israel Cemetery
sentences.chinese: 把骨灰甕埋在新澤西州伊麗莎伯布萊猶太人墓地。

sentences.english: In New Jersey, the ocean surge and rainfall caused severe inland flooding.
sentences.chinese: 在新澤西州，巨大的海浪和強降雨引發了內陸洪災。

sentences.english: Oradell is a borough in Bergen County, New Jersey, United States.
sentences.chinese: 奧拉德爾是美國新澤西州卑爾根縣中的小鎮。

sentences.english: You must confront the sulphurous dystopia of industrial New Jersey.
sentences.chinese: 你只得面對工業化的新澤西州地獄般糟糕的環境。

sentences.english: Gerry and I live in New Jersey, where insurance costs are steep.
sentences.chinese: 格里和我住在汽車保險費用奇高的新澤西州。

sentences.english: The Brownie Extraordinaire is sold in Atlantic City, New Jersey.
sentences.chinese: 這款特製布朗尼是由新澤西州亞特蘭大城推出的。

sentences.english: The freshman at Colonia High School in New Jersey has loved snakes for most of her life.
sentences.chinese: 新澤西州科洛尼亞高中的一名新生在生活中酷愛蛇。

sentences.english: Voters in New Jersey and Virginia will head to the polls to elect governors.
sentences.chinese: 新澤西州和弗吉利亞的選民將投票選出他們的州長。

sentences.english: There are golf - ball - size hails in New Jersey today.
sentences.chinese: 新澤西州今日下起高爾夫球大小的冰雹。

sentences.english: 1787-New Jersey became the third state to ratify the US Constitution.
sentences.chinese: 1787年的今天，新澤西州批准成爲美國第三個州。

sentences.english: Its address was listed at an office in Cranford, New Jersey.
sentences.chinese: 它的地址被列在新澤西州克蘭福德的一個辦公室。

sentences.english: Two winning tickets for Mega Millions Lottery Drawing were sold in New Jersey and Georgia.
sentences.chinese: 在新澤西州和喬治亞州，兩張百萬抽獎券已經售出。
